listitem.para:
Choose a directory where to save the .zip file
              and, after saving, open the file (it may happen, at this point, that a security
              warning message comes out: choose Run anyway);

chapter.para:


how to create a Standard Diagram;



how to create a Freeform Diagram;



how to create a Kin Terms Diagram;



how to create a Query Diagram;



how to deal with the several features related to the above mentioned
            diagrams.

      All the diagrams produced are in a scalable vector format of publishing quality
      and all diagrams can be exported into PDF format. The working files are in SVG (Scalable
      Vector Graphics) format, which can be opened in graphics applications or viewed in modern web
      browsers.

listitem.para:
Line/Dash: the relations line can be either
                    continuous lines or dashed lines, with the dashes being thicker or
                    thinner;

if you have data of your own: File menu >
                      Import Gedcom/CSV/TIP file > choose the
                    necessary file > Open;

Kin Term: here, as the name itself says,
                    you have to enter the kin terms that will also represent the labels of the
                    entities in the diagram;

Referent Kin Type Strings: in this second
                    column you have to enter, for each kin term, its corresponding definition, i.e.
                    the letters listed in Section 2.2, point 2;

to show or hide the whole diagram >
                    respectively check or uncheck the option Generate Example
                      Entities. It is checked by default;

to delete some of the kin terms >
                    check the corresponding little squares on the right of the column Description and click on Delete
                      Selected;

[If you do not already have a project-based diagram open (see section 2.1 above -
              option 'Open Diagram')] From the File menu select
                New Diagram of Type and then Standard Diagram (database driven);

Export as JPEG/PNG/TIFF (File menu) [Note: PDF
            format works!]. These feature fails on the webstart, but it works if KinOath is
            installed;

Propositus Kin Type Strings (File menu > New
            Diagram of Type > Kin Terms Diagram > table on the right of the page > third
            column);
